-- UBS says is collaborating with Belgian authorities in tax case
-- 
-- Thu Jun 19, 2014 07:42AM EDT
-- None



ZURICH, June 19 (Reuters) - UBS <UBSN.VX> said it was fully collaborating with Belgian authorities in an investigation into alleged tax fraud by the Swiss bank's unit.

Belgian prosecutors said on Thursday that the head of UBS Belgium had been detained for questioning in connection with the investigation. [ID:nL6N0P02O2] "UBS is fully collaborating with the Belgium authorities," a spokesman for the bank said in an emailed statement.